COLOUR (preserved specimen, 
Fig. 3B, E–F
). Cephalothorax and chelicerae yellowish brown mottled with grey. Legs and pedipalps yellowish white, without annulations. Black rings around eyes. Abdomen light grey, with white markings.

CHELICERAE. With 3 large widely spaced prolateral teeth (middle tooth largest) (
Fig. 3B
). With faint stridulating ridges. Three small closely spaced retrolateral denticles, positioned between the two first prolateral teeth.

CHELICERA. Cheliceral teeth and stridulation file as in male (
Fig. 3A
).
